{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"There's a poem written"},{"time":2000,"text":"by a very famous English poet"},{"time":4000,"text":"at the end of the 19th century."},{"time":6000,"text":"It was said to echo in Churchill's brain"},{"time":9000,"text":"in the 1930s."},{"time":11000,"text":"And the poem goes:"},{"time":13000,"text":"\"On the idle hill of summer,"},{"time":15000,"text":"lazy with the flow of streams,"},{"time":17000,"text":"hark I hear a distant drummer,"},{"time":19000,"text":"drumming like a sound in dreams,"},{"time":21000,"text":"far and near and low and louder on the roads of earth go by,"},{"time":24000,"text":"dear to friend and food to powder,"},{"time":27000,"text":"soldiers marching,"},{"time":29000,"text":"soon to die.\""},{"time":31000,"text":"Those who are interested in poetry,"},{"time":33000,"text":"the poem is \"A Shropshire Lad\" written by A.E. Housman."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36000,"text":"But what Housman understood,"},{"time":38000,"text":"and you hear it in the symphonies of Nielsen too,"},{"time":42000,"text":"was that the long, hot, silvan summers"},{"time":46000,"text":"of stability of the 19th century"},{"time":48000,"text":"were coming to a close,"},{"time":50000,"text":"and that we were about to move"},{"time":52000,"text":"into one of those terrifying periods of history"},{"time":54000,"text":"when power changes."},{"time":56000,"text":"And these are always periods, ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":58000,"text":"accompanied by turbulence,"},{"time":61000,"text":"and all too often by blood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63000,"text":"And my message for you"},{"time":65000,"text":"is that I believe we are condemned, if you like,"},{"time":67000,"text":"to live at just one of those moments in history"},{"time":70000,"text":"when the gimbals upon which"},{"time":72000,"text":"the established order of power is beginning to change"},{"time":75000,"text":"and the new look of the world,"},{"time":77000,"text":"the new powers that exist in the world,"},{"time":80000,"text":"are beginning to take form."},{"time":82000,"text":"And these are -- and we see it very clearly today --"},{"time":85000,"text":"nearly always highly turbulent times, highly difficult times,"},{"time":88000,"text":"and all too often very bloody times."},{"time":90000,"text":"By the way, it happens about once every century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93000,"text":"You might argue that the last time it happened --"},{"time":95000,"text":"and that's what Housman felt coming and what Churchill felt too --"},{"time":98000,"text":"was that when power passed from the old nations,"},{"time":101000,"text":"the old powers of Europe,"},{"time":103000,"text":"across the Atlantic to the new emerging power"},{"time":105000,"text":"of the United States of America --"},{"time":107000,"text":"the beginning of the American century."},{"time":109000,"text":"And of course, into the vacuum"},{"time":111000,"text":"where the too-old European powers used to be"},{"time":114000,"text":"were played the two bloody catastrophes"},{"time":117000,"text":"of the last century --"},{"time":119000,"text":"the one in the first part and the one in the second part: the two great World Wars."},{"time":122000,"text":"Mao Zedong used to refer to them as the European civil wars,"},{"time":125000,"text":"and it's probably a more accurate way of describing them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128000,"text":"Well, ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":130000,"text":"we live at one of those times."},{"time":132000,"text":"But for us, I want to talk about three factors today."},{"time":135000,"text":"And the first of these, the first two of these,"},{"time":138000,"text":"is about a shift in power."},{"time":140000,"text":"And the second is about some new dimension which I want to refer to,"},{"time":143000,"text":"which has never quite happened in the way it's happening now."},{"time":146000,"text":"But let's talk about the shifts of power that are occurring to the world."},{"time":149000,"text":"And what is happening today"},{"time":151000,"text":"is, in one sense, frightening"},{"time":153000,"text":"because it's never happened before."},{"time":156000,"text":"We have seen lateral shifts of power --"},{"time":158000,"text":"the power of Greece passed to Rome"},{"time":161000,"text":"and the power shifts that occurred"},{"time":163000,"text":"during the European civilizations --"},{"time":166000,"text":"but we are seeing something slightly different."},{"time":168000,"text":"For power is not just moving laterally"},{"time":170000,"text":"from nation to nation."},{"time":172000,"text":"It's also moving vertically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174000,"text":"What's happening today is that the power that was encased,"},{"time":177000,"text":"held to accountability, held to the rule of law,"},{"time":180000,"text":"within the institution of the nation state"},{"time":183000,"text":"has now migrated in very large measure onto the global stage."},{"time":186000,"text":"The globalization of power --"},{"time":188000,"text":"we talk about the globalization of markets,"},{"time":190000,"text":"but actually it's the globalization of real power."},{"time":194000,"text":"And where, at the nation state level"},{"time":196000,"text":"that power is held to accountability"},{"time":198000,"text":"subject to the rule of law,"},{"time":200000,"text":"on the international stage it is not."},{"time":203000,"text":"The international stage and the global stage where power now resides:"},{"time":206000,"text":"the power of the Internet, the power of the satellite broadcasters,"},{"time":209000,"text":"the power of the money changers --"},{"time":212000,"text":"this vast money-go-round"},{"time":214000,"text":"that circulates now 32 times the amount of money necessary"},{"time":218000,"text":"for the trade it's supposed to be there to finance --"},{"time":221000,"text":"the money changers, if you like,"},{"time":223000,"text":"the financial speculators"},{"time":225000,"text":"that have brought us all to our knees quite recently,"},{"time":228000,"text":"the power of the multinational corporations"},{"time":230000,"text":"now developing budgets"},{"time":233000,"text":"often bigger than medium-sized countries."},{"time":235000,"text":"These live in a global space"},{"time":237000,"text":"which is largely unregulated,"},{"time":239000,"text":"not subject to the rule of law,"},{"time":242000,"text":"and in which people may act free of constraint."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244000,"text":"Now that suits the powerful"},{"time":247000,"text":"up to a moment."},{"time":249000,"text":"It's always suitable for those who have the most power"},{"time":252000,"text":"to operate in spaces without constraint,"},{"time":255000,"text":"but the lesson of history is that, sooner or later,"},{"time":258000,"text":"unregulated space --"},{"time":260000,"text":"space not subject to the rule of law --"},{"time":262000,"text":"becomes populated, not just by the things you wanted --"},{"time":265000,"text":"international trade, the Internet, etc. --"},{"time":267000,"text":"but also by the things you don't want --"},{"time":269000,"text":"international criminality, international terrorism."},{"time":272000,"text":"The revelation of 9/11"},{"time":274000,"text":"is that even if you are the most powerful nation on earth,"},{"time":279000,"text":"nevertheless,"},{"time":282000,"text":"those who inhabit that space can attack you"},{"time":284000,"text":"even in your most iconic of cities"},{"time":286000,"text":"one bright September morning."},{"time":288000,"text":"It's said that something like 60 percent"},{"time":290000,"text":"of the four million dollars that was taken to fund 9/11"},{"time":293000,"text":"actually passed through the institutions of the Twin Towers"},{"time":296000,"text":"which 9/11 destroyed."},{"time":298000,"text":"You see, our enemies also use this space --"},{"time":300000,"text":"the space of mass travel, the Internet, satellite broadcasters --"},{"time":303000,"text":"to be able to get around their poison,"},{"time":306000,"text":"which is about destroying our systems and our ways."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309000,"text":"Sooner or later,"},{"time":311000,"text":"sooner or later,"},{"time":313000,"text":"the rule of history"},{"time":315000,"text":"is that where power goes"},{"time":317000,"text":"governance must follow."},{"time":320000,"text":"And if it is therefore the case, as I believe it is,"},{"time":322000,"text":"that one of the phenomenon of our time"},{"time":324000,"text":"is the globalization of power,"},{"time":326000,"text":"then it follows that one of the challenges of our time"},{"time":329000,"text":"is to bring governance to the global space."},{"time":332000,"text":"And I believe that the decades ahead of us now"},{"time":335000,"text":"will be to a greater or lesser extent turbulent"},{"time":339000,"text":"the more or less we are able to achieve that aim:"},{"time":342000,"text":"to bring governance to the global space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344000,"text":"Now notice, I'm not talking about government."},{"time":346000,"text":"I'm not talking about setting up"},{"time":348000,"text":"some global democratic institution."},{"time":351000,"text":"My own view, by the way, ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":353000,"text":"is that this is unlikely to be done"},{"time":355000,"text":"by spawning more U.N. institutions."},{"time":357000,"text":"If we didn't have the U.N., we'd have to invent it."},{"time":359000,"text":"The world needs an international forum."},{"time":361000,"text":"It needs a means by which you can legitimize international action."},{"time":365000,"text":"But when it comes to governance of the global space,"},{"time":367000,"text":"my guess is this won't happen"},{"time":370000,"text":"through the creation of more U.N. institutions."},{"time":372000,"text":"It will actually happen by the powerful coming together"},{"time":375000,"text":"and making treaty-based systems,"},{"time":377000,"text":"treaty-based agreements,"},{"time":379000,"text":"to govern that global space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381000,"text":"And if you look, you can see them happening, already beginning to emerge."},{"time":384000,"text":"The World Trade Organization: treaty-based organization,"},{"time":387000,"text":"entirely treaty-based,"},{"time":389000,"text":"and yet, powerful enough to hold even the most powerful, the United States,"},{"time":392000,"text":"to account if necessary."},{"time":394000,"text":"Kyoto: the beginnings of struggling to create"},{"time":396000,"text":"a treaty-based organization."},{"time":398000,"text":"The G20:"},{"time":400000,"text":"we know now that we have to put together an institution"},{"time":402000,"text":"which is capable of bringing governance"},{"time":404000,"text":"to that financial space for financial speculation."},{"time":407000,"text":"And that's what the G20 is, a treaty-based institution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410000,"text":"Now there's a problem there,"},{"time":412000,"text":"and we'll come back to it in a minute,"},{"time":414000,"text":"which is that if you bring the most powerful together"},{"time":417000,"text":"to make the rules in treaty-based institutions,"},{"time":419000,"text":"to fill that governance space,"},{"time":422000,"text":"then what happens to the weak who are left out?"},{"time":425000,"text":"And that's a big problem,"},{"time":427000,"text":"and we'll return to it in just a second."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429000,"text":"So there's my first message,"},{"time":431000,"text":"that if you are to pass through these turbulent times"},{"time":434000,"text":"more or less turbulently,"},{"time":437000,"text":"then our success in doing that"},{"time":439000,"text":"will in large measure depend on our capacity"},{"time":441000,"text":"to bring sensible governance"},{"time":443000,"text":"to the global space."},{"time":445000,"text":"And watch that beginning to happen."},{"time":448000,"text":"My second point is,"},{"time":450000,"text":"and I know I don't have to talk to an audience like this"},{"time":452000,"text":"about such a thing,"},{"time":454000,"text":"but power is not just shifting vertically,"},{"time":457000,"text":"it's also shifting horizontally."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459000,"text":"You might argue that the story, the history of civilizations,"},{"time":462000,"text":"has been civilizations gathered around seas --"},{"time":465000,"text":"with the first ones around the Mediterranean,"},{"time":468000,"text":"the more recent ones in the ascendents of Western power around the Atlantic."},{"time":472000,"text":"Well it seems to me"},{"time":474000,"text":"that we're now seeing a fundamental shift of power, broadly speaking,"},{"time":477000,"text":"away from nations gathered around the Atlantic [seaboard]"},{"time":480000,"text":"to the nations gathered around the Pacific rim."},{"time":482000,"text":"Now that begins with economic power,"},{"time":484000,"text":"but that's the way it always begins."},{"time":486000,"text":"You already begin to see the development of foreign policies,"},{"time":489000,"text":"the augmentation of military budgets"},{"time":491000,"text":"occurring in the other growing powers in the world."},{"time":494000,"text":"I think actually"},{"time":496000,"text":"this is not so much a shift from the West to the East;"},{"time":498000,"text":"something different is happening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500000,"text":"My guess is, for what it's worth,"},{"time":502000,"text":"is that the United States will remain"},{"time":504000,"text":"the most powerful nation on earth"},{"time":506000,"text":"for the next 10 years, 15,"},{"time":509000,"text":"but the context in which she holds her power"},{"time":512000,"text":"has now radically altered; it has radically changed."},{"time":515000,"text":"We are coming out of 50 years,"},{"time":517000,"text":"most unusual years, of history"},{"time":519000,"text":"in which we have had a totally mono-polar world,"},{"time":522000,"text":"in which every compass needle"},{"time":524000,"text":"for or against"},{"time":526000,"text":"has to be referenced by its position to Washington --"},{"time":529000,"text":"a world bestrode by a single colossus."},{"time":533000,"text":"But that's not a usual case in history."},{"time":535000,"text":"In fact, what's now emerging"},{"time":537000,"text":"is the much more normal case of history."},{"time":539000,"text":"You're beginning to see the emergence"},{"time":541000,"text":"of a multi-polar world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543000,"text":"Up until now,"},{"time":545000,"text":"the United States has been the dominant feature of our world."},{"time":548000,"text":"They will remain the most powerful nation,"},{"time":550000,"text":"but they will be the most powerful nation"},{"time":552000,"text":"in an increasingly multi-polar world."},{"time":554000,"text":"And you begin to see the alternative centers of power building up --"},{"time":557000,"text":"in China, of course,"},{"time":559000,"text":"though my own guess is that China's ascent to greatness is not smooth."},{"time":562000,"text":"It's going to be quite grumpy"},{"time":564000,"text":"as China begins to democratize her society"},{"time":566000,"text":"after liberalizing her economy."},{"time":568000,"text":"But that's a subject of a different discussion."},{"time":571000,"text":"You see India, you see Brazil."},{"time":573000,"text":"You see increasingly"},{"time":575000,"text":"that the world now looks actually, for us Europeans,"},{"time":578000,"text":"much more like Europe in the 19th century."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581000,"text":"Europe in the 19th century:"},{"time":583000,"text":"a great British foreign secretary, Lord Canning,"},{"time":585000,"text":"used to describe it as the \"European concert of powers.\""},{"time":588000,"text":"There was a balance, a five-sided balance."},{"time":590000,"text":"Britain always played to the balance."},{"time":593000,"text":"If Paris got together with Berlin,"},{"time":595000,"text":"Britain got together with Vienna and Rome to provide a counterbalance."},{"time":598000,"text":"Now notice,"},{"time":600000,"text":"in a period which is dominated by a mono-polar world,"},{"time":602000,"text":"you have fixed alliances --"},{"time":604000,"text":"NATO, the Warsaw Pact."},{"time":606000,"text":"A fixed polarity of power"},{"time":608000,"text":"means fixed alliances."},{"time":610000,"text":"But a multiple polarity of power"},{"time":612000,"text":"means shifting and changing alliances."},{"time":614000,"text":"And that's the world we're coming into,"},{"time":616000,"text":"in which we will increasingly see"},{"time":618000,"text":"that our alliances are not fixed."},{"time":620000,"text":"Canning, the great British foreign secretary once said,"},{"time":622000,"text":"\"Britain has a common interest,"},{"time":624000,"text":"but no common allies.\""},{"time":626000,"text":"And we will see increasingly"},{"time":628000,"text":"that even we in the West"},{"time":630000,"text":"will reach out, have to reach out,"},{"time":632000,"text":"beyond the cozy circle of the Atlantic powers"},{"time":634000,"text":"to make alliances with others"},{"time":636000,"text":"if we want to get things done in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639000,"text":"Note, that when we went into Libya,"},{"time":641000,"text":"it was not good enough for the West to do it alone;"},{"time":643000,"text":"we had to bring others in."},{"time":645000,"text":"We had to bring, in this case, the Arab League in."},{"time":648000,"text":"My guess is Iraq and Afghanistan are the last times"},{"time":651000,"text":"when the West has tried to do it themselves,"},{"time":653000,"text":"and we haven't succeeded."},{"time":655000,"text":"My guess"},{"time":657000,"text":"is that we're reaching the beginning of the end of 400 years --"},{"time":660000,"text":"I say 400 years because it's the end of the Ottoman Empire --"},{"time":663000,"text":"of the hegemony of Western power,"},{"time":665000,"text":"Western institutions and Western values."},{"time":669000,"text":"You know, up until now, if the West got its act together,"},{"time":672000,"text":"it could propose and dispose"},{"time":674000,"text":"in every corner of the world."},{"time":676000,"text":"But that's no longer true."},{"time":678000,"text":"Take the last financial crisis"},{"time":680000,"text":"after the Second World War."},{"time":682000,"text":"The West got together --"},{"time":684000,"text":"the Bretton Woods Institution, World Bank, International Monetary Fund --"},{"time":687000,"text":"the problem solved."},{"time":689000,"text":"Now we have to call in others."},{"time":691000,"text":"Now we have to create the G20."},{"time":693000,"text":"Now we have to reach beyond the cozy circle"},{"time":695000,"text":"of our Western friends."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697000,"text":"Let me make a prediction for you,"},{"time":699000,"text":"which is probably even more startling."},{"time":702000,"text":"I suspect we are now reaching the end"},{"time":705000,"text":"of 400 years"},{"time":707000,"text":"when Western power was enough."},{"time":709000,"text":"People say to me, \"The Chinese, of course,"},{"time":711000,"text":"they'll never get themselves involved"},{"time":713000,"text":"in peace-making, multilateral peace-making around the world.\""},{"time":715000,"text":"Oh yes? Why not?"},{"time":717000,"text":"How many Chinese troops"},{"time":719000,"text":"are serving under the blue beret, serving under the blue flag,"},{"time":721000,"text":"serving under the U.N. command in the world today?"},{"time":723000,"text":"3,700."},{"time":725000,"text":"How many Americans? 11."},{"time":728000,"text":"What is the largest naval contingent"},{"time":730000,"text":"tackling the issue of Somali pirates?"},{"time":733000,"text":"The Chinese naval contingent."},{"time":735000,"text":"Of course they are, they are a mercantilist nation."},{"time":737000,"text":"They want to keep the sea lanes open."},{"time":739000,"text":"Increasingly, we are going to have to do business"},{"time":742000,"text":"with people with whom we do not share values,"},{"time":745000,"text":"but with whom, for the moment, we share common interests."},{"time":748000,"text":"It's a whole new different way"},{"time":750000,"text":"of looking at the world that is now emerging."}]},{"cues":[{"time":753000,"text":"And here's the third factor,"},{"time":755000,"text":"which is totally different."},{"time":758000,"text":"Today in our modern world,"},{"time":760000,"text":"because of the Internet,"},{"time":762000,"text":"because of the kinds of things people have been talking about here,"},{"time":765000,"text":"everything is connected to everything."},{"time":769000,"text":"We are now interdependent."},{"time":771000,"text":"We are now interlocked,"},{"time":773000,"text":"as nations, as individuals,"},{"time":775000,"text":"in a way which has never been the case before,"},{"time":777000,"text":"never been the case before."},{"time":780000,"text":"The interrelationship of nations,"},{"time":782000,"text":"well it's always existed."},{"time":784000,"text":"Diplomacy is about managing the interrelationship of nations."},{"time":787000,"text":"But now we are intimately locked together."},{"time":789000,"text":"You get swine flu in Mexico,"},{"time":791000,"text":"it's a problem for Charles de Gaulle Airport"},{"time":793000,"text":"24 hours later."},{"time":795000,"text":"Lehman Brothers goes down, the whole lot collapses."},{"time":798000,"text":"There are fires in the steppes of Russia,"},{"time":801000,"text":"food riots in Africa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":803000,"text":"We are all now deeply, deeply, deeply interconnected."},{"time":807000,"text":"And what that means"},{"time":810000,"text":"is the idea of a nation state acting alone,"},{"time":814000,"text":"not connected with others,"},{"time":816000,"text":"not working with others,"},{"time":818000,"text":"is no longer a viable proposition."},{"time":820000,"text":"Because the actions of a nation state"},{"time":823000,"text":"are neither confined to itself,"},{"time":825000,"text":"nor is it sufficient for the nation state itself"},{"time":827000,"text":"to control its own territory,"},{"time":829000,"text":"because the effects outside the nation state"},{"time":832000,"text":"are now beginning to affect what happens inside them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":835000,"text":"I was a young soldier"},{"time":837000,"text":"in the last of the small empire wars of Britain."},{"time":841000,"text":"At that time, the defense of my country"},{"time":843000,"text":"was about one thing and one thing only:"},{"time":846000,"text":"how strong was our army, how strong was our air force,"},{"time":849000,"text":"how strong was our navy and how strong were our allies."},{"time":851000,"text":"That was when the enemy was outside the walls."},{"time":853000,"text":"Now the enemy is inside the walls."},{"time":856000,"text":"Now if I want to talk about the defense of my country,"},{"time":858000,"text":"I have to speak to the Minister of Health"},{"time":860000,"text":"because pandemic disease is a threat to my security,"},{"time":863000,"text":"I have to speak to the Minister of Agriculture"},{"time":865000,"text":"because food security is a threat to my security,"},{"time":867000,"text":"I have to speak to the Minister of Industry"},{"time":871000,"text":"because the fragility of our hi-tech infrastructure"},{"time":874000,"text":"is now a point of attack for our enemies --"},{"time":876000,"text":"as we see from cyber warfare --"},{"time":878000,"text":"I have to speak to the Minister of Home Affairs"},{"time":881000,"text":"because who has entered my country,"},{"time":883000,"text":"who lives in that terraced house in that inner city"},{"time":886000,"text":"has a direct effect on what happens in my country --"},{"time":888000,"text":"as we in London saw in the 7/7 bombings."},{"time":892000,"text":"It's no longer the case that the security of a country"},{"time":895000,"text":"is simply a matter for its soldiers and its ministry of defense."},{"time":898000,"text":"It's its capacity to lock together its institutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901000,"text":"And this tells you something very important."},{"time":904000,"text":"It tells you that, in fact,"},{"time":906000,"text":"our governments, vertically constructed,"},{"time":909000,"text":"constructed on the economic model of the Industrial Revolution --"},{"time":911000,"text":"vertical hierarchy, specialization of tasks,"},{"time":914000,"text":"command structures --"},{"time":916000,"text":"have got the wrong structures completely."},{"time":918000,"text":"You in business know"},{"time":920000,"text":"that the paradigm structure of our time, ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":922000,"text":"is the network."},{"time":924000,"text":"It's your capacity to network that matters,"},{"time":926000,"text":"both within your governments and externally."}]},{"cues":[{"time":929000,"text":"So here is Ashdown's third law."},{"time":931000,"text":"By the way, don't ask me about Ashdown's first law and second law"},{"time":934000,"text":"because I haven't invented those yet;"},{"time":936000,"text":"it always sounds better if there's a third law, doesn't it?"},{"time":938000,"text":"Ashdown's third law is that in the modern age,"},{"time":941000,"text":"where everything is connected to everything,"},{"time":943000,"text":"the most important thing about what you can do"},{"time":946000,"text":"is what you can do with others."},{"time":948000,"text":"The most important bit about your structure --"},{"time":950000,"text":"whether you're a government, whether you're an army regiment,"},{"time":952000,"text":"whether you're a business --"},{"time":954000,"text":"is your docking points, your interconnectors,"},{"time":956000,"text":"your capacity to network with others."},{"time":958000,"text":"You understand that in industry;"},{"time":960000,"text":"governments don't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":963000,"text":"But now one final thing."},{"time":965000,"text":"If it is the case, ladies and gentlemen -- and it is --"},{"time":968000,"text":"that we are now locked together"},{"time":970000,"text":"in a way that has never been quite the same before,"},{"time":972000,"text":"then it's also the case that we share a destiny with each other."},{"time":976000,"text":"Suddenly and for the very first time,"},{"time":979000,"text":"collective defense, the thing that has dominated us"},{"time":982000,"text":"as the concept of securing our nations,"},{"time":984000,"text":"is no longer enough."},{"time":986000,"text":"It used to be the case"},{"time":988000,"text":"that if my tribe was more powerful than their tribe, I was safe;"},{"time":990000,"text":"if my country was more powerful than their country, I was safe;"},{"time":993000,"text":"my alliance, like NATO, was more powerful than their alliance, I was safe."},{"time":996000,"text":"It is no longer the case."},{"time":998000,"text":"The advent of the interconnectedness"},{"time":1001000,"text":"and of the weapons of mass destruction"},{"time":1003000,"text":"means that, increasingly,"},{"time":1005000,"text":"I share a destiny with my enemy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1007000,"text":"When I was a diplomat"},{"time":1009000,"text":"negotiating the disarmament treaties with the Soviet Union"},{"time":1012000,"text":"in Geneva in the 1970s,"},{"time":1014000,"text":"we succeeded because we understood"},{"time":1016000,"text":"we shared a destiny with them."},{"time":1018000,"text":"Collective security is not enough."},{"time":1021000,"text":"Peace has come to Northern Ireland"},{"time":1023000,"text":"because both sides realized that the zero-sum game couldn't work."},{"time":1026000,"text":"They shared a destiny with their enemies."},{"time":1029000,"text":"One of the great barriers to peace in the Middle East"},{"time":1031000,"text":"is that both sides, both Israel and, I think, the Palestinians,"},{"time":1034000,"text":"do not understand"},{"time":1036000,"text":"that they share a collective destiny."},{"time":1039000,"text":"And so suddenly, ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":1041000,"text":"what has been the proposition"},{"time":1043000,"text":"of visionaries and poets down the ages"},{"time":1046000,"text":"becomes something we have to take seriously"},{"time":1048000,"text":"as a matter of public policy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1050000,"text":"I started with a poem, I'll end with one."},{"time":1053000,"text":"The great poem of John Donne's."},{"time":1056000,"text":"\"Send not for whom the bell tolls.\""},{"time":1060000,"text":"The poem is called \"No Man is an Island.\""},{"time":1062000,"text":"And it goes:"},{"time":1064000,"text":"\"Every man's death affected me,"},{"time":1067000,"text":"for I am involved in mankind,"},{"time":1069000,"text":"send not to ask"},{"time":1071000,"text":"for whom the bell tolls,"},{"time":1073000,"text":"it tolls for thee.\""},{"time":1075000,"text":"For John Donne, a recommendation of morality."},{"time":1078000,"text":"For us, I think,"},{"time":1080000,"text":"part of the equation for our survival."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1083000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1085000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}